Ma passed the exam, but only briefly.
Although his Kuomintang Party (KMT) appoints three of the five mayors, it did not receive a majority vote.
Instead, the Democratic Progress Party (DPP), which advocates greater independence from Taiwan, received almost 50% of the votes, the KMT received 45%.
