Both the police and the state security service are blackmailing high security funds so they can maintain their expensive standard of living in Moscow, it says.
They collect money not only from legitimate businesses, but also from organized criminal gangs.
Every layer of bureaucracy – what Prime Minister Vladimir Putin has called “Vertical of Authority” – takes its share of the money that the ladders migrate upwards.
The memo, which was sent to Washington under the name of Ambassador John Beirle, was published Tuesday by WikiLeaks on its homepage.
The memo is based on sources whose names have been edited.
It was written while Yuri Luzhkov was still the mayor of Moscow, and it accuses him of corruption.
