Affaire Clotilde Reiss: the Elysée Palace exaggerates its mediation function for Syria
Within more than six months, from July 2009 to May 2010, the fate of Clotilde Reiss, a young French researcher detained in Iran for "spying" the French public, put diplomacy on the alert and accentuated the deterioration of relations between Paris and Paris.
All this under the watchful eye of U.S. diplomats.
The American documents obtained by WikiLeaks and reviewed by the newspaper "Le Monde" give some background to this crisis.
They describe how the Elysée explained its strategy to the Americans, who went so far as to give these advice on how to deal with their own crisis of “hostage taking” in Iran (a small group of migrants).
